subSubSection.paragraph:
Larval description.
The description is based on tadpoles at Gosner Stage 35 (n = 1; 
Fig. 1
). Body ovoid in both lateral and dorsal views; dorsally, body mostly flattened and medially depressed; slightly concave on the ventral side; body length 33% of total length; snout rounded both in dorsal and lateral view. Eyes positioned and oriented dorsolateral. External nares placed equidistant from snout and eye; narial openings oval with the margin slightly elevated and no ornamentation; inter-nostril distance 57% of inter-orbital distance. Spiracle dextral opening posterolaterally, positioned midway along the body length and on the lower side of lateral mid-body; inner wall present and attached to the body wall. Vent tube short and opened on the dextral side. Tail length about 67% of the total length; shape lanceolate; tail musculature width moderate with the broadest width about 36% of the maximum body width; height broadest at body tail junction tapering to the tail tip; dorsal fin taller than the ventral fin and both fins tapering posteriorly to a pointed tail tip. Origin of the dorsal fin at body tail junction and the ventral fin at ventral terminus; the greatest tail height is about mid length. Oral disc anteroventrally located and emarginated (
Fig. 1D
); oral disc width 38% of maximum body width; marginal papillae restricted to the lateral corners and the lower labium, with wide gap on the upper labium; marginal papillae in double row; small submarginal papillae only in commissures. Labial tooth row formula (LTRF) 6(3–6)/3(1); lengths of the labial teeth rows are A1=A2=P1=P2=P3>A3>A4>A5>A6. Upper jaw sheath as a broad arc with a wide medial portion and narrow lateral corners; lower jaw sheath V-shaped with a wide median region and thin lateral corners; keratinization strong and margins uniformly serrated. In preservative, dorsal body olive with no blotches; gular, abdominal and lateral body region translucent and immaculate; gut coils visible; caudal region immaculate and tail fins opaque; tail musculature and fins subtly mottled with brown spots.
